{"TopicId":208936,"ForumId":104,"TopicTitle":"SIMPLE Part Failure!/Reliability Mod?","CreatedByName":"kerbmario","CreatedById":221047,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-11T12:44:02Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kerbmario","CreatedById":221047,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-11T12:44:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to have some sort of Failures with Aircraft Engines (for example i wanna add support for such thing to My mod)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe mod should\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-just include basic failure system (or it should have availability to turn anything besides failures off)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-it should not be a big mod\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBonus:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the mod can do particles or animations when the part fails, it would be a bonus \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ETL;DR: Searching for Simple Part Failure Mod\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CarelessDoughnut","CreatedById":213281,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-11T21:47:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOhScrap! and DangIt! are the one I\u0027m aware of, but not sure of how simple they are to make compatible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022190933\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8663490190\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/192360-112x-ohscrap-a-scrapyard-based-part-failure-and-reliability-mod-2200-prerelease2021-jul-19/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8904170088\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/178973-112x-dang-it-continued/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOhScrap seems to have different modules for each failure type:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E@PART[*]:HAS[@MODULE[ModuleEngines*]:HAS[!PROPELLANT[SolidFuel]]]:NEEDS[OhScrap,ScrapYard]:FOR[OhScrap]\n{\n    MODULE\n    {\n        name = EngineFailureModule\n        baseChanceOfFailure = 0.11\n        expectedLifetime = 6\n        spaceEngineBaseChanceOfFailure = 0.1\n        spaceEngineExpectedLifetime = 3\n    }\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zer0Kerbal","CreatedById":190933,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-12T03:39:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224153888\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022208936\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221657576022\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022213281\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CarelessDoughnut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, CarelessDoughnut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOhScrap! and DangIt\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Eand they really are overdue for some tlc\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Ethey are about as simple and straightforward (playwise) and can be.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}